library(tidyverse)
library(janitor)

housing_raw <- read_csv("data/kc_house_data.csv") %>% 
  select(-c(`date`, `id`, `sqft_living15`, `sqft_lot15`, `zipcode`))
Rows: 21613 Columns: 21── Column specification ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Delimiter: ","
chr   (1): id
dbl  (19): price, bedrooms, bathrooms, sqft_living, sqft_lot, floors, waterfron...
dttm  (1): date
ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
housing <- housing_raw %>% 
  mutate(waterfront = as.logical(waterfront)) %>% 
  mutate(yr_renovated = as.logical(if_else(yr_renovated > 0, TRUE, FALSE))) %>% 
  mutate(grade = case_when(
    grade < 4 ~ "low",
    grade < 10 ~ "average",
    TRUE ~ "high"
  )) %>% 
  mutate(view = case_when(
    view == 0 ~ "zero",
    view == 1 ~ "one",
    view == 2 ~ "two",
    view == 3 ~ "three",
    view == 4 ~ "four"
  )) %>% 
  select(-sqft_above)
  
  
alias( price ~ ., housing)

Model :
price ~ bedrooms + bathrooms + sqft_living + sqft_lot + floors + 
    waterfront + view + condition + grade + sqft_above + sqft_basement + 
    yr_built + yr_renovated + lat + long

library(modelr)

housing_resid <- housing %>% 
  add_residuals(lm4c) 


housing_resid %>% 
  select(-c(price, grade, sqft_living, bathrooms, lat)) %>% 
  ggpairs()
coplot(resid ~ log(sqft_living) | grade,
       panel = function(x, y, ...){
         points(x, y)
         abline(lm(y ~ x), col = "blue")
       },
       data = housing_resid, rows = 1)
